From c440478eb1dfda8221b3ac9e38d0ee2815fb9bbd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: LiangCheng Wang <zaq14760@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 15:32:29 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] configs: kakip-es1_defconfig: increase LMB regions for
 reserved memory

Increase CONFIG_LMB_MAX_REGIONS to 16 so U-Boot has enough LMB entries
for the Kakip reserved-memory layout.

Remote processor support can add more reserved-memory entries to
the DT passed to Linux. Keeping a larger LMB table avoids
boot-time reservation failures when those regions are present.
---
 configs/kakip-es1_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configs/kakip-es1_defconfig b/configs/kakip-es1_defconfig
index afe3f8ea..d125ef4d 100644
--- a/configs/kakip-es1_defconfig
+++ b/configs/kakip-es1_defconfig
@@ -93,3 +93,4 @@ CONFIG_CMD_SPI=y
 CONFIG_SPI_FLASH_STMICRO=y
 CONFIG_DM_SPI_FLASH=y
 CONFIG_ENV_SECT_SIZE=0x20000
+CONFIG_LMB_MAX_REGIONS=16
-- 
2.34.1

